Vice President Mike Pence visited Rockport, Texas, almost a year after Hurricane Harvey hit the region. He reassured the community that the Trump administration is committed to working with Texas to rebuild and recover from the hurricane. Pence thanked the first responders and volunteers for their efforts in helping the community rebuild. He also acknowledged the significant amount of resources that have been provided to the region, including over $35 billion in disaster relief and recovery funding. Pence expressed pride in the government's response but emphasized the importance of neighbor-to-neighbor support and the role of faith-based organizations in the recovery process. He encouraged the community to continue their efforts and promised ongoing support from the federal government. Pence concluded by expressing faith in the leadership of President Trump, Texas Governor Greg Abbott, and the resilience of the community.